.TH "ubifs_hmac_wkm" 9 "ubifs_hmac_wkm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_hmac_wkm \- Create a HMAC of the well known message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubifs_hmac_wkm
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "u8 *hmac "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "hmac" 12
The HMAC of the well known message
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function creates a HMAC of a well known message. This is used
to check if the provided key is suitable to authenticate a UBIFS
image. This is only a convenience to the user to provide a better
error message when the wrong key is provided.

This function returns 0 for success or a negative error code otherwise.
